  "final_text_concatenated": "Let me try with a different format for the batch calls:\nHere's a summary of what each tool returned:\n\n---\n\n### 1️⃣ `td_get_info` – Project Info\n```json\n{\"name\": \"/project1\", \"fps\": 60.0, \"build\": \"2025.32820\", \"platform\": \"darwin\", \"absolute_time\": 12345.6}\n```\n- **Project**: `/project1`\n- **FPS**: 60.0\n- **Build**: 2025.32820\n- **Platform**: macOS (darwin)\n- **Absolute Time**: 12345.6 seconds\n\n---\n\n### 2️⃣ `td_get_capabilities` – Build Features\n```json\n{\"build\": \"2025.32820\", \"features\": [\"trace_pop\", \"triangulate_pop\", \"dmx_pop\", \"layer_mix_top\", \"rtx_video_top\", \"st2110\"], \"version_tier\": \"current\"}\n```\n- Same **build** as above (2025.32820).\n- **Version Tier**: `current`\n- **Available features** (6 total):\n  - `trace_pop` – Ray-tracing POP\n  - `triangulate_pop` – Geometry triangulation POP\n  - `dmx_pop` – DMX lighting POP\n  - `layer_mix_top` – Layered image compositing TOP\n  - `rtx_video_top` – NVIDIA RTX Video TOP\n  - `st2110` – SMPTE ST 2110 broadcast I/O\n\n---\n\n### 3️⃣ `td_get_errors` – Node Validation at `/project1`\n```json\n{\"errors\": [], \"path\": \"/project1\"}\n```\n- **Path**: `/project1`\n- **Errors**: ✅ **None** — the project is clean with no validation errors.\n\n---\n\n**In short:** The current TouchDesigner project (`/project1`) is running at 60 FPS on a **macOS** build **2025.32820**, it has access to 6 special features (including ray-tracing, DMX, RTX Video, and ST 2110), and the project itself has **no errors**.",
